Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
copyObject(25.10)                                            copyObject(25.10)

Name
       copyObject

Syntax
        copyObject

       [-help]

       Copies the selected placement or routing blockages. Use the pasteObject
       command  to  paste  the copied object to the required location. You can
       use the copyObject command any time after floorplanning the design. You
       can also copy selected placement and routing blockages from the GUI  by
       using  the  Copy tool. To access the Copy tool, choose Edit - Copy from
       the menu bar or press F3 after clicking the Copy widget () on the tool-
       bar.

       Note: The copyObject command currently works  only  for  placement  and
       routing blockages. Use the editCopy command to copy wires or vias.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the copyObject command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man copyObject

       Example
              * The  following  commands copy and paste the selected placement
                and routing blockages:

                copyObject

                pasteObject -loc 10 20

Related Information
              * pasteObject

              * editCopy

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

